WEBVTT

1
00:00:27.590 --> 00:00:28.999
Who are you?
What do you want?

2
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:30.309
Hello. sir.

3
00:00:30.310 --> 00:00:32.590
I'm DI Scanlon. This is DS Stone.

4
00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:35.269
We'd like to see some
identification. please.

5
00:00:35.270 --> 00:00:37.470
This is my mother's house.
There's nothing here.

6
00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:39.830
Liar.

7
00:00:41.440 --> 00:00:42.740
Get back!

8
00:00:43.590 --> 00:00:45.820
-Is anyone else in the house?
-Just my mother.

9
00:00:47.030 --> 00:00:48.759
<i>You do not have to say anything.</i>

10
00:00:48.760 --> 00:00:52.480
<i>but it may harm your defence if you
do not mention when questioned...</i>

11
00:00:56.780 --> 00:00:58.080
<i>Alan?</i>

12
00:01:08.350 --> 00:01:10.509
Where's Alan?

13
00:01:10.510 --> 00:01:11.810
<i>Alan?</i>

14
00:01:21.750 --> 00:01:23.050
Carol?

15
00:01:24.050 --> 00:01:25.450
Carol Taft?

16
00:01:40.890 --> 00:01:42.190
DS Stone?

17
00:01:43.350 --> 00:01:45.350
-Sir.
-Well done.

18
00:01:48.610 --> 00:01:51.119
Hold a briefing for
the murder of a drug addict.

19
00:01:51.120 --> 00:01:52.849
you can't pay them to turn up.

20
00:01:52.850 --> 00:01:54.649
Mention the word serial killer

21
00:01:54.650 --> 00:01:56.859
and suddenly
you need extra chairs.

22
00:01:56.860 --> 00:01:58.470
Multiple murderer.

23
00:01:59.610 --> 00:02:01.619
You've done plenty of these before?

24
00:02:01.620 --> 00:02:03.430
No. Never.

25
00:02:03.940 --> 00:02:08.190
Follow my lead and remember.
it's a good news day.

26
00:02:13.150 --> 00:02:15.679
And Alan Harvey
would undoubtedly

27
00:02:15.680 --> 00:02:17.609
have killed more
than three women

28
00:02:17.610 --> 00:02:20.539
if it wasn't for some exemplary
police work.

29
00:02:20.540 --> 00:02:23.379
Particularly from DS Stone here.

30
00:02:23.380 --> 00:02:26.090
who will talk you through the arrest.

31
00:02:30.130 --> 00:02:32.470
Carol Taft should be alive.

32
00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:39.420
Can you expand
on that. sir?

33
00:02:40.210 --> 00:02:43.699
What DS Stone means
is despite this success.

34
00:02:43.700 --> 00:02:46.559
it's no time for a celebration.

35
00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:48.760
What I mean is if we had treated

36
00:02:49.070 --> 00:02:51.629
each woman as part of a pattern.

37
00:02:51.630 --> 00:02:54.239
rather than separate
missing persons cases.

38
00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:56.729
we would have found Alan Harvey
sooner.

39
00:02:56.730 --> 00:02:59.300
And Carol Taft would still be alive.

40
00:02:59.800 --> 00:03:01.670
And we failed.

41
00:03:02.980 --> 00:03:04.280
I failed.

42
00:03:27.980 --> 00:03:31.339
So...
you believe Homicide Command

43
00:03:31.340 --> 00:03:34.390
should be workingmore
closely with Missing Persons.

44
00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:38.149
Yes.

45
00:03:38.150 --> 00:03:40.829
Yes. most people that go missing
are vulnerable.

46
00:03:40.830 --> 00:03:44.089
And we need to be looking at them
the way Alan Harvey did.

47
00:03:44.090 --> 00:03:45.979
as potential victims.

48
00:03:45.980 --> 00:03:47.389
Otherwise. we'll...

49
00:03:47.390 --> 00:03:49.190
we'll be too late again.

50
00:03:51.220 --> 00:03:53.300
You start on Monday.

51
00:03:54.760 --> 00:03:56.069
Sir?

52
00:03:56.070 --> 00:03:59.649
The strategic outcome of this
case is your permanent secondment

53
00:03:59.650 --> 00:04:03.950
to Missing Persons.
looking for serial killers.

54
00:04:07.200 --> 00:04:09.069
You're telling me I'm leaving?

55
00:04:09.070 --> 00:04:10.649
I'm telling you...

56
00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:13.650
you're finished.
DS Stone.

57
00:04:17.860 --> 00:04:20.920
Now...
get out.

58
00:04:39.330 --> 00:04:43.170
Chasing Shadows
Part 1 of 4

59
00:04:46.330 --> 00:04:49.310
Subtitles by Deluxe
Sync: Marocas62

60
00:05:33.310 --> 00:05:34.610
Leanne?

61
00:05:43.110 --> 00:05:44.410
Leanne?

62
00:06:38.650 --> 00:06:40.319
Morning. Ruth.
Coffee's up.

63
00:06:40.320 --> 00:06:42.289
Morning. Sal.
Can you ask Eric

64
00:06:42.290 --> 00:06:44.089
to resend that study
on the elderly?

65
00:06:44.090 --> 00:06:46.059
I thought it was about pensions
and deleted it.

66
00:06:46.060 --> 00:06:47.490
Sure. will do.

67
00:06:54.100 --> 00:06:58.419
Hi. I'm Ruth Hattersley.
one of the senior analysts here.

68
00:06:58.420 --> 00:07:00.780
I believe we're going
to be working together.

69
00:07:01.590 --> 00:07:03.829
That's me. over there.

70
00:07:03.830 --> 00:07:05.589
You are DS Stone...

71
00:07:05.590 --> 00:07:07.500
Is it all right if I call you Sean?

72
00:07:10.950 --> 00:07:15.090
You're booked in
for an induction at... ten.

73
00:07:15.450 --> 00:07:18.180
I'll take you to meet
everybody first.

74
00:07:19.010 --> 00:07:21.450
We're really excited
about you being here.

75
00:07:22.590 --> 00:07:24.089
It's long overdue.

76
00:07:24.090 --> 00:07:26.499
Obviously we advise the police
all the time.

77
00:07:26.500 --> 00:07:28.369
but we never get to do
any field work.

78
00:07:28.370 --> 00:07:31.490
-Do you have a husband?
-No.

79
00:07:32.550 --> 00:07:34.289
No. I...
I don't.

80
00:07:34.290 --> 00:07:36.390
I do have a son...

81
00:07:37.440 --> 00:07:40.229
..who is ridiculously excited
about the fact

82
00:07:40.230 --> 00:07:41.969
that I'm going to be working
with someone

83
00:07:41.970 --> 00:07:45.689
who is as fascinated
by serial killers as he is.

84
00:07:45.690 --> 00:07:48.120
Multiple murderer.
And I'm not fascinated.

85
00:07:49.390 --> 00:07:52.419
But you are looking
into those missing persons

86
00:07:52.420 --> 00:07:55.629
most at risk of becoming victims
of serial killers?

87
00:07:55.630 --> 00:07:57.190
Multiple murderer.

88
00:07:57.830 --> 00:08:00.000
I'm so sorry. What's the difference?

89
00:08:00.710 --> 00:08:02.669
Serial killers live in Hollywood.

90
00:08:02.670 --> 00:08:05.229
Multiple murderer helps keep them
where they belong.

91
00:08:05.230 --> 00:08:08.229
-Which is where?
-Right next door.

92
00:08:08.230 --> 00:08:09.539
They're not fascinating.

93
00:08:09.540 --> 00:08:12.590
They're not evil geniuses.
most are merely opportunist.

94
00:08:13.290 --> 00:08:17.269
So...
where do we start?

95
00:08:17.270 --> 00:08:21.009
Well. I've looked at every low
and medium risk missing person

96
00:08:21.010 --> 00:08:23.509
reported in the region
over the past three months.

97
00:08:23.510 --> 00:08:25.839
I've focused on the
five groups most often

98
00:08:25.840 --> 00:08:27.689
targeted by UK multiple murderers.

99
00:08:27.690 --> 00:08:29.879
-Which are?
-Ask your son.

100
00:08:29.880 --> 00:08:31.589
it sounds like he would know.

101
00:08:31.590 --> 00:08:33.879
We're left with those.

102
00:08:33.880 --> 00:08:38.419
We need to focus on her.
Taylor Davis. aged 16.

103
00:08:38.420 --> 00:08:40.299
Why isn't she high priority?

104
00:08:40.300 --> 00:08:42.809
Because she's run away
three times in the last year.

105
00:08:42.810 --> 00:08:45.809
But she always returns
between hours 24 and 30.

106
00:08:45.810 --> 00:08:47.499
We're now in hour 60.
No sightings.

107
00:08:47.500 --> 00:08:49.529
no phone.
no social media activity.

108
00:08:49.530 --> 00:08:51.979
-How long have you been here?
-We're creatures of habit.

109
00:08:51.980 --> 00:08:53.680
That's what creates patterns.

110
00:08:53.990 --> 00:08:56.789
Taylor broke hers. Do you have a car?

111
00:08:56.790 --> 00:08:59.490
I'm going to see Taylor's
investigating officer.

112
00:09:21.410 --> 00:09:23.150
What the hell...?

113
00:09:43.730 --> 00:09:47.529
-Why didn't we travel together?
-I think while I drive.

114
00:09:47.530 --> 00:09:49.789
What's a medium risk runaway
got to do with me?

115
00:09:49.790 --> 00:09:51.679
-Because she's high risk.
-Not according to this.

116
00:09:51.680 --> 00:09:54.929
That's why I'm here. You have to
prioritise Taylor Davis immediately.

117
00:09:54.930 --> 00:09:57.369
Is that before or after I look
for whoever slashed a boy's throat

118
00:09:57.370 --> 00:09:59.379
last night for his phone?

119
00:09:59.380 --> 00:10:02.589
Or for the man sexually assaulting
women in the toilets of the local A&E?

120
00:10:02.590 --> 00:10:03.939
-Is he dead?
-Who?

121
00:10:03.940 --> 00:10:05.249
The boy.

122
00:10:05.250 --> 00:10:07.029
-No. but...
-Before. then.

123
00:10:07.030 --> 00:10:09.539
-Where' she going? Where you going?
-To see Taylor's mother.

124
00:10:09.540 --> 00:10:11.759
No. you are not.
You are not!

125
00:10:11.760 --> 00:10:13.869
If anyone's going to speak to her.
it's going to be me.

126
00:10:13.870 --> 00:10:16.070
-Sir. can l have aword?
-Not now. Raymond.

127
00:10:21.170 --> 00:10:23.750
I'm sorry about this.
having to drive me.

128
00:10:24.210 --> 00:10:26.499
There's no point
in us taking three cars.

129
00:10:26.500 --> 00:10:29.119
Do you know him?
DS Stone?

130
00:10:29.120 --> 00:10:30.610
By reputation only.

131
00:10:30.960 --> 00:10:33.890
He seems to have decided not
to like me.

132
00:10:34.850 --> 00:10:37.400
How long have you two
been working together?

133
00:10:38.590 --> 00:10:41.389
-Two hours.
-Sorry.

134
00:10:41.390 --> 00:10:43.910
I know. it should take slightly
longer.

135
00:10:44.790 --> 00:10:47.309
-It's not you.
-You think?

136
00:10:47.310 --> 00:10:48.619
I know.

137
00:10:48.620 --> 00:10:50.689
DS Stone marches to the beat
of his own drum.

138
00:10:50.690 --> 00:10:52.869
I'm not entirely sure
if it's medical

139
00:10:52.870 --> 00:10:54.570
but it's definitely not personal.

140
00:10:55.380 --> 00:10:57.169
I thought
this was an opportunity.

141
00:10:57.170 --> 00:10:58.899
Oh. this is an opportunity.

142
00:10:58.900 --> 00:11:01.209
It's an opportunity
for Homicide Command

143
00:11:01.210 --> 00:11:04.229
to dump what they see
as a liability onto Missing Persons.

144
00:11:04.230 --> 00:11:05.770
No offence.

145
00:11:06.520 --> 00:11:07.929
You know.
finding the missing.

146
00:11:07.930 --> 00:11:09.569
telling their
families they're safe.

147
00:11:09.570 --> 00:11:11.099
that's why I do this job.

148
00:11:11.100 --> 00:11:14.350
I thought this was going to be a chance
to find the ones who aren't safe.

149
00:11:14.880 --> 00:11:16.899
Well. look on the bright side.

150
00:11:16.900 --> 00:11:19.560
-What's that?
-You got to ride with me.

151
00:11:33.030 --> 00:11:34.650
I'll lead. OK?

152
00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:36.909
Hi. Miss Davis.
I'm DI Prior.

153
00:11:36.910 --> 00:11:38.919
I'm afraid there's no news
about Taylor.

154
00:11:38.920 --> 00:11:42.009
I'm Ruth from Missing Persons. He's
not keeping anything from you.

155
00:11:42.010 --> 00:11:43.310
Come in.

156
00:11:47.140 --> 00:11:48.980
Does Taylor
have a college bag?

157
00:11:49.590 --> 00:11:52.899
This is it. She took it with her
and some clothes and stuff

158
00:11:52.900 --> 00:11:56.650
the other times she went. but PC
Stanley's already been through it.

159
00:11:57.360 --> 00:12:00.039
He said detectives
only come if it's suspicious.

160
00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:03.359
Yeah. I just need to make
sure nothing was missed. that's all.

161
00:12:03.360 --> 00:12:05.509
So Taylor was last seen by you.
Mr. Legg.

162
00:12:05.510 --> 00:12:07.860
wearing the jeans.
trainers and the red jacket.

163
00:12:08.590 --> 00:12:10.540
-Yeah.
-Tay went to college as usual.

164
00:12:11.040 --> 00:12:12.909
Did all her classes.

165
00:12:12.910 --> 00:12:14.629
But she never came back.

166
00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:17.329
13 to 17 year olds go missing
more than anyone else.

167
00:12:17.330 --> 00:12:19.239
Most don't go far
and come back quickly.

168
00:12:19.240 --> 00:12:20.540
But she hasn't.

169
00:12:21.220 --> 00:12:23.649
And she never missed
college the other times.

170
00:12:23.650 --> 00:12:26.290
Do we know where Taylor went
on those other occasions?

171
00:12:27.460 --> 00:12:30.750
Look. it's not always been easy
between me and Taylor.

172
00:12:31.490 --> 00:12:34.440
When she came back. I thought...
we thought. it was best left...

173
00:12:35.290 --> 00:12:38.169
-I did.
-You've phoned all her friends?

174
00:12:38.170 --> 00:12:41.489
Those we know of.
We gave PC Stanley a list.

175
00:12:41.490 --> 00:12:43.189
Is there a boyfriend?

176
00:12:43.190 --> 00:12:45.950
-Where's her phone?
-She hasn't got one.

177
00:12:46.470 --> 00:12:50.350
She lost it sometime last week.
I can't remember when exactly.

178
00:12:51.070 --> 00:12:54.069
I know she was unhappy about it.
She lived on that thing.

179
00:12:54.070 --> 00:12:55.790
Has she got bad breath?

180
00:12:57.680 --> 00:12:59.809
-What the hell was that. DS Stone?
-What?

181
00:12:59.810 --> 00:13:02.169
Have you any idea
how they're feeling?

182
00:13:02.170 --> 00:13:04.399
-No.
-So you'll prioritise Taylor?

183
00:13:04.400 --> 00:13:06.309
-On what grounds?
-That she's at least as likely

184
00:13:06.310 --> 00:13:08.550
to have been abducted
as she is to have run away.

185
00:13:18.720 --> 00:13:20.099
Jumpin.

186
00:13:43.450 --> 00:13:48.319
Sean! I am not going to phone you
again to find out where you are.

187
00:13:48.320 --> 00:13:50.939
You have to tell me
what you're doing.

188
00:13:50.940 --> 00:13:53.099
I'm waiting for someone from
Taylor's class

189
00:13:53.100 --> 00:13:54.960
to take me to her tutor room.

190
00:13:55.870 --> 00:13:59.580
I. sort of.
meant before you actually do it.

191
00:14:02.110 --> 00:14:04.310
So is this where we're interviewing
them?

192
00:14:05.910 --> 00:14:07.219
Who?

193
00:14:07.220 --> 00:14:09.480
Taylor's friends.
That's why we're...

194
00:14:12.250 --> 00:14:15.269
Why are we here. Sean?

195
00:14:15.270 --> 00:14:17.819
Because mobile phones
continue to emit a signal

196
00:14:17.820 --> 00:14:20.619
even after they've been switched off
or taken to pieces.

197
00:14:20.620 --> 00:14:22.369
I ran a trace.

198
00:14:22.370 --> 00:14:24.259
Taylor's phone is somewhere
in this building.

199
00:14:24.260 --> 00:14:25.659
Are you police?

200
00:14:25.660 --> 00:14:28.869
-Yes. who are you?
-Sophie. Sophie Scarrow.

201
00:14:28.870 --> 00:14:30.490
-Ruth Hattersley.
-Hi.

202
00:14:33.700 --> 00:14:35.509
So you know Taylor Davis?

203
00:14:35.510 --> 00:14:38.749
Yeah. we have a few classes
together. that's about it.

204
00:14:38.750 --> 00:14:43.160
Did she ever talk to you about
any problems she might be having?

205
00:14:43.570 --> 00:14:46.189
We don't really talk about anything.

206
00:14:46.190 --> 00:14:48.100
-You do know she's missing?
-Yeah.

207
00:14:48.510 --> 00:14:51.140
Any idea where she might go?

208
00:14:51.850 --> 00:14:53.860
I said. we don't really talk.

209
00:14:54.870 --> 00:14:59.070
-Who are her friends?
-To be honest. she don't really have any.

210
00:15:00.780 --> 00:15:02.460
You got visitors. sir.

211
00:15:03.090 --> 00:15:05.379
Are you here about Taylor?
Any news?

212
00:15:05.380 --> 00:15:08.019
Do the students have their own desks
or lockers.

213
00:15:08.020 --> 00:15:09.909
places they can store things?

214
00:15:09.910 --> 00:15:12.589
-No. Why?
-We need to find Taylor's phone.

215
00:15:12.590 --> 00:15:15.609
-I've got it.
-Have you?

216
00:15:15.610 --> 00:15:18.399
She's been warned not to use it
during lessons over and over again

217
00:15:18.400 --> 00:15:19.980
but she kept on doing it.

218
00:15:20.360 --> 00:15:22.879
-so I took it from her.
-When?

219
00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:24.519
Last Thursday.

220
00:15:24.520 --> 00:15:26.199
I told her on Friday
she could have it back

221
00:15:26.200 --> 00:15:27.709
after the weekend.
but...

222
00:15:27.710 --> 00:15:30.819
-obviously with everything that's been going on...
-Been in the drawer the whole time?

223
00:15:30.820 --> 00:15:32.579
I couldn't have known
what she was planning.

224
00:15:32.580 --> 00:15:35.250
-And you haven't tampered with it?
-Of course not.

225
00:15:38.070 --> 00:15:39.949
It's locked.
We need her code.

226
00:15:39.950 --> 00:15:41.429
Have you tried her birthday?

227
00:15:41.430 --> 00:15:43.389
I alternate between
my son's birthday

228
00:15:43.390 --> 00:15:45.379
and the day
I got my decree nisi.

229
00:15:45.380 --> 00:15:47.169
-What codes do you use?
-Why?

230
00:15:47.170 --> 00:15:49.309
The whole point of a code
is it's meant to be secret.

231
00:15:49.310 --> 00:15:51.319
-Right.
-If I told you. I'd have to change it.

232
00:15:51.320 --> 00:15:54.120
-What would be the point of that?
-Yep. yep. OK. forgetit.

233
00:15:54.630 --> 00:15:56.649
-What?
-Van Gogh.

234
00:15:56.650 --> 00:15:58.400
-Date of birth?
-No...

235
00:16:00.970 --> 00:16:02.270
Death.

236
00:16:07.590 --> 00:16:09.659
Sean. this is Angela Bale.

237
00:16:09.660 --> 00:16:12.269
She's Director of the
Missing Persons... Bureau.

238
00:16:12.270 --> 00:16:14.019
Your new boss.

239
00:16:14.020 --> 00:16:19.470
So that's DS Stone. who didn't
come to meet me this morning.

240
00:16:20.480 --> 00:16:21.879
I think so.

241
00:16:21.880 --> 00:16:24.459
He hasn't actually
introduced himself to me yet

242
00:16:24.460 --> 00:16:28.519
or shared anything other than the
fact that he prefers to drive alone.

243
00:16:28.520 --> 00:16:31.479
I've yet to meet the person
that you can't connect with.

244
00:16:31.480 --> 00:16:34.730
Well. you would have done...
if he hadn't ignored you.

245
00:16:46.760 --> 00:16:49.950
Taylor spent a lot of time
on one website.

246
00:16:51.370 --> 00:16:53.290
IMC.

247
00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:00.850
"It's my choice".

248
00:17:01.160 --> 00:17:05.269
It's a suicide website
used to talk about how to do it.

249
00:17:05.270 --> 00:17:07.089
Not very good advice.

250
00:17:07.090 --> 00:17:09.770
Otherwise there wouldn't
be a website. they'd all be dead.

251
00:17:10.380 --> 00:17:13.850
Join... as a 16-year-old girl.

252
00:17:22.620 --> 00:17:26.650
Since when did suicide
become a club to join?

253
00:17:53.210 --> 00:17:56.849
Maybe it's not a suicide website
at all.

254
00:17:56.850 --> 00:17:58.399
Maybe it's actually

255
00:17:58.400 --> 00:18:02.829
a place for isolated kids
to contact each other

256
00:18:02.830 --> 00:18:06.829
and that actually prevents them...
..from killing themselves

257
00:18:06.830 --> 00:18:09.769
-Hello. can I help you?
-Who are you?

258
00:18:09.770 --> 00:18:12.719
Kay... Amos?
Mr. Prior sent me.

259
00:18:12.720 --> 00:18:15.219
He said you're looking into
suspicious missing persons.

260
00:18:15.220 --> 00:18:16.609
-Yes. we are.
-But he knows

261
00:18:16.610 --> 00:18:18.489
we're busy at the moment.

262
00:18:18.490 --> 00:18:21.950
-If you could leave your contact details...
-There. that's Chloe.

263
00:18:22.810 --> 00:18:26.449
That's my daughter.
Why have you crossed her out?

264
00:18:26.450 --> 00:18:29.289
-That doesn't mean anything.
-Yes. it does.

265
00:18:29.290 --> 00:18:31.959
Every week for months
I've been going to that station

266
00:18:31.960 --> 00:18:33.599
and every week they mug me off!

267
00:18:33.600 --> 00:18:35.529
Because she's 20
and an adult

268
00:18:35.530 --> 00:18:37.169
with a history of drug
abuse and absconding.

269
00:18:37.170 --> 00:18:38.479
That is Chloe. isn't it?

270
00:18:38.480 --> 00:18:40.099
That's your excuse
for doing nothing?

271
00:18:40.100 --> 00:18:42.389
No. That's why the police
haven't prioritised her.

272
00:18:42.390 --> 00:18:45.309
Plus the fact you told them
she said she wasn't coming back.

273
00:18:45.310 --> 00:18:48.179
-Yeah. but she didn't mean it.
-Why did she say it then?

274
00:18:48.180 --> 00:18:50.529
Because people do when they row.
She always says it.

275
00:18:50.530 --> 00:18:52.709
-Maybe this time is different.
-That's what I'm saying!

276
00:18:52.710 --> 00:18:54.729
Someone's took her.
I know they did.

277
00:18:54.730 --> 00:18:56.509
I've got no evidence.

278
00:18:56.510 --> 00:18:59.359
but I know...
I know something's wrong.

279
00:18:59.360 --> 00:19:02.219
Kay. the reality is that
most of the people on that wall.

280
00:19:02.220 --> 00:19:04.360
they'll turn up alive and well.

281
00:19:05.150 --> 00:19:08.900
Chloe always phones me.
even if it's only to shout at me.

282
00:19:10.330 --> 00:19:13.610
Someone's took her
and even if she...

283
00:19:15.660 --> 00:19:18.050
I just want her back with me.

284
00:19:18.390 --> 00:19:21.990
I can't get on...
not until I know everything. I...

285
00:19:29.050 --> 00:19:31.919
It's not even an up-to-date picture.

286
00:19:31.920 --> 00:19:33.229
I'm so sorry.

287
00:19:33.230 --> 00:19:35.589
-if you could just leave your de...
-Don't bother!

288
00:19:35.590 --> 00:19:37.879
It is a suicide site.

289
00:19:37.880 --> 00:19:41.579
I need more time to decipher
her usernames but...

290
00:19:41.580 --> 00:19:45.549
at least one of the kids on here
has killed himself recently.

291
00:19:45.550 --> 00:19:49.759
He was found six weeks ago.
disused printworks.

292
00:19:49.760 --> 00:19:53.669
Kieran Gandley. aged 17.

293
00:19:53.670 --> 00:19:57.099
He joined IMC three months
before Taylor.

294
00:20:18.850 --> 00:20:20.460
I'm home!

295
00:20:20.810 --> 00:20:22.449
-They didn't have any shallots...
-Mum!

296
00:20:22.450 --> 00:20:25.109
Mum. what happened?
..so I got you some onions instead.

297
00:20:25.110 --> 00:20:27.520
-Well?
-Hello. darling.

298
00:20:28.310 --> 00:20:30.470
-How was school?
-Mum!

299
00:20:31.490 --> 00:20:32.809
Don't try and distract me.

300
00:20:32.810 --> 00:20:35.689
Did you or did you not
meet the serial killer?

301
00:20:35.690 --> 00:20:37.569
Multiple murderer.

302
00:20:37.570 --> 00:20:40.399
Well. technically. multiple murderer
is an umbrella term

303
00:20:40.400 --> 00:20:43.049
encompassing spree killers.
serial killers and mass murderers.

304
00:20:43.050 --> 00:20:46.019
-So. is that a yes?
-Let her get in the door. Bryan!

305
00:20:46.020 --> 00:20:48.409
-Everything all right?
-Mum!

306
00:20:48.410 --> 00:20:50.269
Don't pester!

307
00:20:50.270 --> 00:20:52.929
But. look. I can help!
Come on. ask me anything.

308
00:20:52.930 --> 00:20:56.770
OK.
How did your maths test go?

309
00:20:59.740 --> 00:21:03.990
-You did do the maths test?
-Yes. I did the maths test.

310
00:21:07.230 --> 00:21:08.530
All right.

311
00:21:08.960 --> 00:21:11.770
I was told to ask you...

312
00:21:12.270 --> 00:21:15.019
What are the five groups
most often targeted

313
00:21:15.020 --> 00:21:17.189
by UK serial killers?

314
00:21:17.190 --> 00:21:21.689
Prostitutes. gay men. the elderly.
kids and runaways.

315
00:21:21.690 --> 00:21:23.049
That's in no particular order.

316
00:21:23.050 --> 00:21:24.799
Did you want them
in any particular order?

317
00:21:24.800 --> 00:21:27.799
Serial killers are not fascinating.
Bryan.

318
00:21:27.800 --> 00:21:32.380
They're not evil geniuses.
most are merely opportunist.

319
00:21:33.780 --> 00:21:36.029
Go on. do your homework.

320
00:21:36.030 --> 00:21:40.490
More importantly.
what's DS Stone like?

321
00:21:41.350 --> 00:21:45.039
Probably as close
as I'll ever get to an actual psycho.

322
00:21:45.040 --> 00:21:47.250
-Who is?
-No one!

323
00:21:48.560 --> 00:21:49.869
It's ironic.

324
00:21:49.870 --> 00:21:53.169
Apparently. he's known
for making connections but...

325
00:21:53.170 --> 00:21:56.329
-Handsome?
-Mum. I am so not interested.

326
00:21:56.330 --> 00:21:59.760
I wasn't asking for you.
Is he married?

327
00:22:00.510 --> 00:22:03.669
Well. if anyone did accidentally
marry him.

328
00:22:03.670 --> 00:22:05.449
it wouldn't have lasted long.

329
00:22:05.450 --> 00:22:08.850
Well. you're the expert. sweetheart.

330
00:22:21.250 --> 00:22:23.450
-Yeah. you phoned the office?
-Yes.

331
00:22:24.650 --> 00:22:26.359
Are you here about that lad?

332
00:22:26.360 --> 00:22:29.389
The boy they say killed himself?
Kieran Gandley?

333
00:22:29.390 --> 00:22:31.570
-That's right.
-Yeah. I remember him.

334
00:22:36.510 --> 00:22:38.529
Yeah. it was me who found him.

335
00:22:38.530 --> 00:22:40.110
Come on. I'll show you.

336
00:22:42.130 --> 00:22:43.439
Yeah. I told him...

337
00:22:43.440 --> 00:22:46.560
I told the boss.
it's too easy to get in.

338
00:22:46.880 --> 00:22:50.130
And I'm not here all the while. the
amount of young kids I've chased off.

339
00:22:50.480 --> 00:22:51.789
I mean. I said.

340
00:22:51.790 --> 00:22:54.590
"You need to sort it
before something bad happens."

341
00:22:56.140 --> 00:22:58.100
Yeah. I don't know why you're back.
but...

342
00:22:59.020 --> 00:23:01.129
but I can show you the emails
that I've sent.

343
00:23:01.130 --> 00:23:02.430
They're all dated.

344
00:23:03.440 --> 00:23:05.940
Think they've offered me
any emotional support?

345
00:23:07.610 --> 00:23:08.910
No.

346
00:23:14.530 --> 00:23:15.830
Just this way.

347
00:23:17.980 --> 00:23:21.270
Yeah. he was in one of these.

348
00:23:22.010 --> 00:23:23.990
I'm not sure which one.

349
00:23:24.890 --> 00:23:26.190
Yeah.

350
00:23:27.500 --> 00:23:28.800
This is it.

351
00:23:31.370 --> 00:23:33.520
Yep. there.

352
00:23:34.110 --> 00:23:36.770
He was on the floor with a rope
around his neck.

353
00:23:37.130 --> 00:23:39.989
You said.
"the boy they say killed himself".

354
00:23:39.990 --> 00:23:41.889
You doubt it was suicide?

355
00:23:41.890 --> 00:23:43.590
Who cares what I think.

356
00:23:43.990 --> 00:23:45.489
I mean.
kids got in all the while.

357
00:23:45.490 --> 00:23:48.389
-How?
-Just climbed the fence.

358
00:23:48.390 --> 00:23:50.379
That razor wire wasn't up then.

359
00:23:50.380 --> 00:23:52.399
Who knows what they were doing
up here.

360
00:23:52.400 --> 00:23:55.440
I warned the boss.
I can prove I did.

361
00:24:21.490 --> 00:24:25.950
Well...
Tell me all about it.

362
00:24:26.380 --> 00:24:29.119
Kieran will have known
from the website

363
00:24:29.120 --> 00:24:31.589
that hanging is the more painful way
to die.

364
00:24:31.590 --> 00:24:35.169
but in the end. suicidal
and homicidal ligature strangulation

365
00:24:35.170 --> 00:24:37.130
look notoriously alike.

366
00:24:40.210 --> 00:24:43.519
-You didn't mean that. did you?
-No.

367
00:24:43.520 --> 00:24:46.189
What is she like.
your new colleague?

368
00:24:46.190 --> 00:24:49.169
40s. five foot eight.
she has a Rolodex.

369
00:24:49.170 --> 00:24:51.610
Yeah. but what was she like. Sean?

370
00:24:53.200 --> 00:24:54.509
Like?

371
00:24:54.510 --> 00:24:57.339
Did you ask lots of questions.
as we said?

372
00:24:57.340 --> 00:24:59.150
Straightaway.
"Have you got a husband?"

373
00:25:01.090 --> 00:25:04.099
Well. that was right. wasn't it?

374
00:25:04.100 --> 00:25:07.129
Do you remember.
I told you to be careful?

375
00:25:07.130 --> 00:25:09.609
She maybe feel awkward.

376
00:25:09.610 --> 00:25:11.980
She might think you're interested.

377
00:25:12.750 --> 00:25:15.290
-Romantically.
-Why?

378
00:25:16.350 --> 00:25:19.229
Never mind.
Anything else?

379
00:25:19.230 --> 00:25:22.509
-She has a son.
-Very-good. Name?

380
00:25:22.510 --> 00:25:24.380
-She didn't say.
-Did you ask?

381
00:25:24.850 --> 00:25:26.150
No.

382
00:25:28.590 --> 00:25:30.319
Your dinner is in the fridge.

383
00:25:30.320 --> 00:25:33.469
And I didn't have time to iron
today.

384
00:25:33.470 --> 00:25:37.100
so I'll bring it on Thursday.
OK?

385
00:25:43.420 --> 00:25:44.720
Wallet?

386
00:25:54.870 --> 00:25:56.170
Bye-bye.

387
00:25:57.250 --> 00:25:58.550
Bye.

388
00:26:02.870 --> 00:26:04.729
"Last seen near Greenwich"

389
00:26:04.730 --> 00:26:06.330
"Walks with assistance"
"MS sufferer"

390
00:26:22.300 --> 00:26:23.950
Who's Taylor?

391
00:26:24.460 --> 00:26:27.229
If you're actually practising
creeping up on people.

392
00:26:27.230 --> 00:26:28.929
I'm going to start worrying.

393
00:26:28.930 --> 00:26:31.579
-What are you doing?
-Nothing.

394
00:26:31.580 --> 00:26:33.879
And why are you calling yourself
Emma?

395
00:26:33.880 --> 00:26:36.879
Listen. when you go online

396
00:26:36.880 --> 00:26:39.999
and read about murder and stuff.

397
00:26:40.000 --> 00:26:44.769
you don't ever...
look at dark stuff. do you?

398
00:26:44.770 --> 00:26:46.929
Define dark. Mum.

399
00:26:46.930 --> 00:26:52.399
Some people go on the web because it
seems like everything is there.

400
00:26:52.400 --> 00:26:54.779
all the answers are
at your fingertips.

401
00:26:54.780 --> 00:26:58.439
Mum. are you going to rant on about
how you and Dad had to split up

402
00:26:58.440 --> 00:27:00.700
-because it was the only option again?
-No!

403
00:27:01.550 --> 00:27:03.339
Why bring him up?

404
00:27:03.340 --> 00:27:07.579
-Why are you on a suicide forum?
-You've seen IMC before?

405
00:27:07.580 --> 00:27:09.819
Look. I look at all types of stuff
on the internet.

406
00:27:09.820 --> 00:27:11.690
What do you want me to say?

407
00:27:12.560 --> 00:27:15.879
That you are not
and never will be one of those kids

408
00:27:15.880 --> 00:27:19.899
whose mothers find out too late
how lost you were.

409
00:27:19.900 --> 00:27:22.909
Mum. I promise...

410
00:27:22.910 --> 00:27:26.170
you will always
know how lost I am.

411
00:27:49.190 --> 00:27:51.090
Five minutes.

412
00:27:58.210 --> 00:27:59.910
-Hello. Donna.
-Hi.

413
00:28:00.370 --> 00:28:02.660
I thought working might help.

414
00:28:03.530 --> 00:28:05.130
I was wondering...

415
00:28:05.840 --> 00:28:07.809
Was there anything to suggest
that Taylor

416
00:28:07.810 --> 00:28:11.170
might have been feeling low
recently?

417
00:28:11.880 --> 00:28:14.399
-Depressed.
-She had her moods.

418
00:28:14.400 --> 00:28:17.220
she's a teenager.
But nothing special. Why?

419
00:28:17.930 --> 00:28:21.819
But there have been problems
in the past. with Graham. yes?

420
00:28:21.820 --> 00:28:24.239
It took Tay a bit of time
to accept things.

421
00:28:24.240 --> 00:28:25.689
when we got together.

422
00:28:25.690 --> 00:28:28.849
We'd been on our own
for so long after her dad died.

423
00:28:28.850 --> 00:28:31.709
but things were settling down.
We were all getting along.

424
00:28:31.710 --> 00:28:33.490
I thought we were.

425
00:28:34.210 --> 00:28:36.750
Graham loves her to bits.
you know.

426
00:28:39.820 --> 00:28:41.780
What is it that
you don't want to tell me?

427
00:28:44.430 --> 00:28:48.109
There are some kids.
teenagers.

428
00:28:48.110 --> 00:28:50.329
who are spending time
on suicide websites...

429
00:28:50.330 --> 00:28:51.630
Suicide?

430
00:28:52.210 --> 00:28:55.350
It doesn't necessarily mean
that Taylor has hurt herself...

431
00:28:55.810 --> 00:28:59.639
There's no way Taylor would ever...
No way.

432
00:28:59.640 --> 00:29:01.419
A girl in her class at college

433
00:29:01.420 --> 00:29:03.729
told us that Taylor has no friends.

434
00:29:03.730 --> 00:29:05.250
Who said that?

435
00:29:05.740 --> 00:29:08.309
-Sophie Scarrow?
-Sophie?

436
00:29:08.310 --> 00:29:10.249
-Yeah.
-She's been Taylor's best friend

437
00:29:10.250 --> 00:29:12.350
since primary school.
They're like sisters.

438
00:29:13.520 --> 00:29:16.390
-You're sure about that?
-Absolutely.

439
00:29:18.530 --> 00:29:21.539
I went to see Donna. to tell her
about the suicide website.

440
00:29:21.540 --> 00:29:25.149
Forget suicide.
Taylor showed no sign of self-harm

441
00:29:25.150 --> 00:29:27.969
or any other suicidal behaviour.
Her GP says the same.

442
00:29:27.970 --> 00:29:31.889
Sophie Scarrow lied.
Taylor is her best friend.

443
00:29:31.890 --> 00:29:33.929
And why should we forget suicide?

444
00:29:33.930 --> 00:29:36.389
I went to the printworks
where Kieran Gandley was found.

445
00:29:36.390 --> 00:29:39.299
The only way in was over a ten-foot
fence and he was suffering from MS.

446
00:29:39.300 --> 00:29:42.700
-I had to do some research...
-Why didn't you tell me any of this?

447
00:29:43.180 --> 00:29:45.959
-Why. do you know about MS?
-No!

448
00:29:45.960 --> 00:29:47.919
I don't think that boy
could have got inside

449
00:29:47.920 --> 00:29:49.529
without someone pulling him
over that fence.

450
00:29:49.530 --> 00:29:52.539
Why didn't you share with me
what you're doing?

451
00:29:52.540 --> 00:29:56.409
-What for?
-Because we work together.

452
00:29:56.410 --> 00:29:58.769
That's what people who
work together do. Sean.

453
00:29:58.770 --> 00:30:00.680
They communicate.

454
00:30:01.040 --> 00:30:03.360
Let's talk about it later.

455
00:30:08.810 --> 00:30:11.489
-Sean.
-This isn't later. this is still now.

456
00:30:11.490 --> 00:30:12.999
At least tell me where we're going

457
00:30:13.000 --> 00:30:14.569
so I don't have to
keep following you.

458
00:30:14.570 --> 00:30:17.390
-To see Sophie. You said she lied.
-To the college.

459
00:30:18.170 --> 00:30:20.269
I'm here to help you.

460
00:30:20.270 --> 00:30:23.909
Yes. The other day
when I asked you about your husband.

461
00:30:23.910 --> 00:30:26.150
I don't find you attractive.

462
00:30:56.080 --> 00:30:58.639
Why did you tell us
you and Taylor aren't friends?

463
00:30:58.640 --> 00:30:59.949
Cos we're not.

464
00:30:59.950 --> 00:31:01.939
-Well. not any more anyway.
-You were friends. weren't you?

465
00:31:01.940 --> 00:31:04.169
-So you lied.
-We haven't spoken in ages.

466
00:31:04.170 --> 00:31:07.399
Hello. Sophie. We wanted to ask you
if you knew anything

467
00:31:07.400 --> 00:31:09.850
about a suicide website.

468
00:31:10.590 --> 00:31:13.420
You don't think Taylor's committed
suicide. do you?

469
00:31:16.640 --> 00:31:19.369
I mean. she's...
she's just gone off. hasn't she?

470
00:31:19.370 --> 00:31:21.270
Why did you two stop talking?

471
00:31:23.170 --> 00:31:24.470
Why?

472
00:31:25.130 --> 00:31:26.579
There was a boy.

473
00:31:26.580 --> 00:31:28.830
So why didn't you tell us
that before?

474
00:31:29.740 --> 00:31:32.000
-Who is he?
-No one.

475
00:31:34.640 --> 00:31:38.379
Hangs round out the front.
Bit older.

476
00:31:38.380 --> 00:31:41.459
Selling cannabis to teenage girls.
including Taylor.

477
00:31:41.460 --> 00:31:44.569
And she used mouthwash to disguise
the smell. didn't she?

478
00:31:44.570 --> 00:31:45.950
What's his name?

479
00:31:46.730 --> 00:31:50.059
Sophie. we think Taylor
might be in very real danger.

480
00:31:50.060 --> 00:31:51.520
What's his name?

481
00:31:52.750 --> 00:31:54.079
-Aaron Scobie.
-Who?

482
00:31:54.080 --> 00:31:56.090
Aaron Scobie!

483
00:32:05.740 --> 00:32:07.759
<i>-Prior.</i>
-Carl. we've got a name.

484
00:32:07.760 --> 00:32:09.729
It's an older boy
Taylor had a crush on.

485
00:32:09.730 --> 00:32:11.639
He's called Aaron Scobie.

486
00:32:11.640 --> 00:32:14.400
<i>Yeah. I know him.
I know where he'll be. Thanks.</i>

487
00:32:34.790 --> 00:32:36.800
<i>Yes. bruv!
Yes.</i>

488
00:32:39.250 --> 00:32:41.050
<i>Here we go. here we go. here we go!</i>

489
00:32:43.310 --> 00:32:45.190
<i>You going down town later?</i>

490
00:32:54.130 --> 00:32:56.400
You're mates of Aaron Scobie's.
aren't you?

491
00:33:01.610 --> 00:33:02.910
Gotcha.

492
00:33:05.210 --> 00:33:07.330
Run!
Police!

493
00:33:13.190 --> 00:33:15.300
-Get off!
-Hey.hey!

494
00:33:15.910 --> 00:33:18.059
-I haven't got anything!
-I'm not interested.

495
00:33:18.060 --> 00:33:19.999
What ever he's said.
he's lying!

496
00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:21.309
What did he say?

497
00:33:21.310 --> 00:33:23.829
We've known each other long enough
to know I ask the questions.

498
00:33:23.830 --> 00:33:25.179
Where's Aaron Scobie?

499
00:33:25.180 --> 00:33:28.209
-With you.
-What?

500
00:33:28.210 --> 00:33:30.899
He got picked up outside his flat
half an hour ago.

501
00:33:30.900 --> 00:33:32.200
By who?

502
00:33:32.570 --> 00:33:35.970
He said he was a detective.
but he was well weird.

503
00:33:39.770 --> 00:33:41.599
Who was he. then?

504
00:34:03.070 --> 00:34:05.179
Do you know Taylor Davis?

505
00:34:05.180 --> 00:34:06.889
I know of her.

506
00:34:06.890 --> 00:34:09.690
I mean.
I've seen her...at the college.

507
00:34:10.270 --> 00:34:11.840
-What's that?
-What?

508
00:34:12.150 --> 00:34:13.930
Around your neck.

509
00:34:15.310 --> 00:34:17.710
-What do you think it is?
-Show me.

510
00:34:25.970 --> 00:34:27.969
Why have you got Taylor Davis's ring?

511
00:34:27.970 --> 00:34:30.029
-I found it.
-No. you didn't.

512
00:34:30.030 --> 00:34:31.339
Where did you get it from?

513
00:34:31.340 --> 00:34:34.499
All right. she was messing about with it
when we were talking and left it behind.

514
00:34:34.500 --> 00:34:36.389
-You do know her?
-I forgot to give it back.

515
00:34:36.390 --> 00:34:37.690
Stop lying!

516
00:34:38.070 --> 00:34:40.529
Taylor has been missing now
for four days.

517
00:34:40.530 --> 00:34:43.919
Statistically.
every hour that passes
makes it less likely she will return.

518
00:34:43.920 --> 00:34:46.149
-Taylor's missing?
-Yes! What do you know about that?

519
00:34:46.150 --> 00:34:48.850
-l hardly knew her!
-We know Taylor was attracted to you.

520
00:34:50.590 --> 00:34:52.749
-Who told you that?
-Where is she. Aaron?

521
00:34:52.750 --> 00:34:54.949
I don't know. I mean. why would I?

522
00:34:54.950 --> 00:34:57.789
You should be speaking to her mates.
people she talks to.

523
00:34:57.790 --> 00:34:59.669
-Like who?
-I don't know!

524
00:34:59.670 --> 00:35:02.320
-She's got new friends. hasn't she?
-Names.

525
00:35:04.130 --> 00:35:07.299
Leanne. isn't it.
she's always on about?

526
00:35:07.300 --> 00:35:09.410
-Well. who's she?
-A word. DS Stone.

527
00:35:16.310 --> 00:35:19.829
In what world do you think it's OK
to arrest and interview a prisoner

528
00:35:19.830 --> 00:35:21.869
with a case with my name on it.
and not tell me?

529
00:35:21.870 --> 00:35:23.329
-He's not under arrest.
-Sean...

530
00:35:23.330 --> 00:35:26.439
Was there a Leanne in the list
of friends Taylor's mother supplied?

531
00:35:26.440 --> 00:35:28.359
I'm a DI. DS Stone.
Do not ignore me.

532
00:35:28.360 --> 00:35:30.359
I'm trying to stop you ignoring
a missing teenager

533
00:35:30.360 --> 00:35:32.299
-before we find her body.
-We need evidence.

534
00:35:32.300 --> 00:35:34.150
Do you have any
evidence against him?

535
00:35:34.510 --> 00:35:36.270
He has Taylor Davis's ring.

536
00:35:37.340 --> 00:35:40.180
-Does he have an explanation?
-Yes. but l don't believe him.

537
00:35:42.130 --> 00:35:43.589
Get out of my sight.

538
00:35:43.590 --> 00:35:45.870
Why are you suddenly
wearing lipstick?

539
00:35:47.240 --> 00:35:48.849
Chief Super...
Wait one second.

540
00:35:48.850 --> 00:35:50.850
Chief Superintendant Drayton.
please.

541
00:35:52.310 --> 00:35:53.610
DI Prior.

542
00:35:54.960 --> 00:35:58.110
OK. well. tell him to call me when
he gets in. thank you.

543
00:35:58.890 --> 00:36:00.699
Ruth. I'm really sorry about that.

544
00:36:00.700 --> 00:36:03.709
You know. I'm happy to work with
you. more than happy. in fact.

545
00:36:03.710 --> 00:36:05.329
But I...
I can't have that. OK?

546
00:36:05.330 --> 00:36:06.899
Yeah.

547
00:36:06.900 --> 00:36:09.450
Davis. can you escort
Miss Hattersley out. please?

548
00:36:20.310 --> 00:36:22.029
Sean!

549
00:36:22.030 --> 00:36:23.480
If this is going to work...

550
00:36:23.990 --> 00:36:27.400
you have to show you're willing to
collaborate with the Bureau.

551
00:36:27.930 --> 00:36:32.180
ie me...and with the police.
ie Carl.

552
00:36:32.690 --> 00:36:35.709
-Who's Carl?
-DI Prior.

553
00:36:35.710 --> 00:36:38.019
I don't think he likes me.

554
00:36:38.020 --> 00:36:40.619
The only way we're going
to find Taylor Davis

555
00:36:40.620 --> 00:36:44.349
is by making real connections. Sean.

556
00:36:44.350 --> 00:36:46.949
by building relationships.

557
00:36:46.950 --> 00:36:49.269
We'll find her by going back
to the suicide website

558
00:36:49.270 --> 00:36:51.350
and looking for Taylor's friend.
Leanne.

559
00:36:53.860 --> 00:36:57.790
Has it never occurred
to you that sometimes...

560
00:36:58.270 --> 00:37:01.990
other people might have something
valuable to offer?

561
00:37:03.650 --> 00:37:04.950
No.

562
00:37:08.350 --> 00:37:10.649
Then I don't think I can help you
after all.

563
00:37:10.650 --> 00:37:12.590
I don't need your help.

564
00:37:15.010 --> 00:37:19.729
By the way. multiple murderer
is actually an umbrella term

565
00:37:19.730 --> 00:37:25.080
encompassing mass murderers.
spree killers and serial killers.

566
00:38:10.030 --> 00:38:11.800
Bryan!

567
00:38:12.630 --> 00:38:13.930
Yeah?

568
00:38:15.070 --> 00:38:17.489
You've been sending emails...
as me.

569
00:38:17.490 --> 00:38:19.649
Not as you.
As Emma.

570
00:38:19.650 --> 00:38:23.329
You left yourself logged in and I make
a much better teenage girl than you.

571
00:38:23.330 --> 00:38:24.999
You...
you talked about Taylor.

572
00:38:25.000 --> 00:38:27.169
Yeah. but nothing you hadn't said
already.

573
00:38:27.170 --> 00:38:30.290
only that she showed you the site
and that you missed her and...

574
00:38:31.630 --> 00:38:35.000
This is an ongoing police
investigation. Bryan.

575
00:38:39.410 --> 00:38:41.450
I'm...
I'm sorry.

576
00:38:45.550 --> 00:38:47.350
It's Leanne again.

577
00:38:50.960 --> 00:38:52.460
LEANNE: U gon quiet. u OK?

578
00:38:53.370 --> 00:38:54.670
EMMA: Hi

579
00:39:00.640 --> 00:39:02.480
LEANNE: Want 2 Meet or No?

580
00:39:06.690 --> 00:39:08.220
EMMA: Where?

581
00:39:30.130 --> 00:39:32.980
"Deceased. Found dead due to
strangulation. Suspected suicide."

582
00:39:39.310 --> 00:39:41.819
I've tried both your phones.
You never answer.

583
00:39:41.820 --> 00:39:44.119
The profile I created
on the suicide website

584
00:39:44.120 --> 00:39:47.060
has been getting messages
from a friend of Taylor's.

585
00:39:47.670 --> 00:39:50.140
We're going to meet now.
At Everfields.

586
00:39:50.550 --> 00:39:52.480
It's Leanne.

587
00:39:53.140 --> 00:39:55.740
Data isn't everything. Sean.

588
00:39:59.330 --> 00:40:02.879
<i>-This is Ruth. leave a message.</i>
-I've found another one.

589
00:40:02.880 --> 00:40:06.669
Lucas Storey. aged 16. released
from a young offenders' institute

590
00:40:06.670 --> 00:40:09.379
four months ago and found dead
two months later

591
00:40:09.380 --> 00:40:11.999
in a derelict office block
having strangled himself.

592
00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:15.429
Lucas. Kieran Gandley and Taylor
Davis have one friend in common.

593
00:40:15.430 --> 00:40:18.189
who had contact with all of them
the day before they went missing.

594
00:40:18.190 --> 00:40:21.060
Leanne. It's a pattern.
Where are you?

595
00:40:23.230 --> 00:40:24.959
<i>You have one new message.</i>

596
00:40:24.960 --> 00:40:27.409
<i>I've tried both your phones.
You never answer.</i>

597
00:40:27.410 --> 00:40:29.569
<i>The profile I created
on the suicide website</i>

598
00:40:29.570 --> 00:40:32.389
<i>has been getting messages
from a friend of Taylor's.</i>

599
00:40:32.390 --> 00:40:34.919
<i>We're going to meet now.
At Everfields.</i>

600
00:40:34.920 --> 00:40:36.220
<i>It's Leanne.</i>

601
00:40:38.930 --> 00:40:41.200
This is Ruth.
leave a message.

602
00:40:48.870 --> 00:40:50.170
Hello?

603
00:41:06.870 --> 00:41:08.770
Hello?
Leanne?

604
00:42:04.610 --> 00:42:05.910
Leanne?

605
00:42:16.650 --> 00:42:19.269
-Hey! Hold up!
-That's not Taylor!

606
00:42:19.270 --> 00:42:21.260
That's not Taylor.
where is she then?

607
00:42:29.050 --> 00:42:30.359
Liar.

608
00:42:30.360 --> 00:42:33.119
-They want me out.
-They need you.

609
00:42:33.120 --> 00:42:35.879
-And where were you at noon today?
-At work until one.

610
00:42:35.880 --> 00:42:38.349
Driving.
I have to cover about 20 sites.

611
00:42:38.350 --> 00:42:42.709
Tay is loved so don't hurt her.

612
00:42:42.710 --> 00:42:44.560
<i>Please don't hurt her.</i>

613
00:42:47.070 --> 00:42:48.379
Taylor.

614
00:42:48.380 --> 00:42:51.360
